I"'<ol>
  <li>In a pan on a medium heat, add the coconut oil and onions. Let it cook until tender.</li>
  <li>Add the rice and mix with the oil and onion to coat the grains in oil.</li>
  <li>Add the vegetable stock and stir it while letting it simmer. It should take approximately 20 minutes for the rice to be absorbed.</li>
  <li>While cooking the rice add the salt, pepper, lemon juice and zest. Mix until well combined.</li>
  <li>In a food processor, add the 80g of cooked peas with 2 tablespoons of water. Blend until the mixture turns into a puree.</li>
  <li>When the rice is cooked remove from the heat and add the basil.</li>
  <li>Add to the rice the pea puree and the 250g of fresh peas. Mix well until combined.</li>
  <li>Serve with a drizzle of olive oil and grated parmesan cheese.</li>
</ol>
